<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Tordail Farstryder</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Nov 2003<br />
	Location: Halas, N.C.
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Do we play the same game? Summer on Karana is one of the busiest times for the server, since the kids are out of school and playing more often. When kids went back to school in August/September, things really quieted down for us. (That was a blessing and a curse, lol -- fewer folks to contend with, but fewer open raids.) The time between Thanksgiving and New Year's is one of the quiet times, when folks are out with family and such. The holiday season most certainly does have a rather large impact on the size of the playerbase. That cannot be ignored, and it is not "rediculous" (sic). <br />
<br />
Our server's bazaar usually runs between 300 and 350 traders. It fluctuates, of course, but that's about average. It seems irresponsible to use bazaar trader population as your sole reason (your initial post) for insisting there are population problems. To be sure, there are fewer players now than there were pre-GOD/WOW/EQ2, but Karana hardly resembles a ghost town in need of a server merge.<br />
<br />
When folks come back after the holiday season and things have calmed down from the new games that are out (you know, the whole the-pixels-are-greener thing ... folks rush out to try the new thing, some don't like it as well as the old, and come back to the old or go find something else to do), then folks can take a look at the playerbase size and determine if it's time to pester SOE for server merges.<br />
<br />
/bow</p>
	
	
	
