<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Gildanni</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Apr 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I'm on the BB server, and yea, I've noticed a drop in population.  But I've also noticed that recently, I'm suddenly getting tells for groups when I'm not even /lfg ON.   Last night, in the space of 30 minutes, I had 6 tells, (I was already in a group)  Yes, I've noticed that the bazaar has dropped in population.  That there are more open spots in PoP zones.  ALot of it is to the good.  I'm in a very casual friendly guild on BB.  It's been around since almost the beginning of EQ. Those of you on BB, might recognize Clan Mackintosh.  Recently, we've experienced an upsurge in applications for those wanting to return to just playing for fun, and the occaisional raid.  We don't want to become one of the Uber raiding guilds.  We have too much fun just grouping with guildmates and friends to really worry, but we are still getting decent upgrades.  We are getting some LDoN's done.  We've gone into OoW.  Gates? eh.. so so on them.  Our level range from lowbies that are just for fun, to level 70 Time equipped players.  No one is complaining about the lack of anything to do.  Almost every place we go to, whether it is in PoP, OoW, or old world, we have our pick of camps.<br />
<br />
I agree with those that say hang on to yer horses.  January/Febuary may see an uprise in the population.  I myself tried the beta of WoW, and others, and always came back to EQ.  Not everyone that left will return.  So be it.  Come next year, SOE just might do something and start merging some of the lower populated servers.  There are plenty still on BB though, so I doubt that it will be one of the first to be merged.<br />
<br />
Only time will really tell <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
