<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Blazz</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Fateseer<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2003<br />
	Location: Upstate, NY
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Just my 2 cents, but I felt the servers were always WAY overpopulated anyway. I have a bias though, because I am on bertoxx, and I was burdened with being the "first server alphabetically" for a LONG LONG time. We have always had a big population. <br />
<br />
I think most people are seeing this as "the twenty 60+ guilds on my server are WAY down" instead of "we sure dont need 20 guilds now, 10 will be plenty". <br />
<br />
More are going to leak, thats for sure, but anyone who says they havent seen this type of thing in the past must not have been playing in an active guild. I saw it with DAoC, with Diablo 2, with SWG. Granted, this is the BIGGEST hit I have seen EQ take, and I agree with Gart that the Gates debacle was a huge factor in the decision of a lot of people to just /cancel and head to another game forever. But OoW certainly helped re-establish EQ as a solid contender in the overall scheme of the MMORPG market, despite its datedness. <br />
<br />
I am giving it til Feb-March til I worry about what SOE is going to do about servers, but honestly, at least speaking for Bertoxx, we dont NEED to add more people from another serrver, we just need to re-align the people who are still playing a bit. Two of the top 4 guilds on Bert are already discussing a merge. People from guilds that had borderline raid attendance in the past are trickling into the guilds that have been able to maintain a semi-regular schedule. When the smoke clears, I can see Bert as having 2-3 UBER High end guilds (instead of 4), 2-3 Time-Ikky guilds (instead of 4) and 2-3 EPish guilds (instead of 4). But theres certainly enough people playing to keep moving along just fine, at least on Bert.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=639568" target="_blank">Blazz, 70 Troll Shaman, Bertoxx</a><br />
