<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Jaradis</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Catabrie Fatewielder</b><br /><i>This whole 'looks its the xmas season' its gonna be quiet thing is rediculous. If anything more people are on during winter than at any other time during the year. Attendance doesnt improve by february, if you havent got the players on now, when its cold, damp and miserable outside you certainly arent going to have them on when the weather improves and then heading into summer when most would rather be sat in their back gardens than in their back rooms.<br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Wow, what a narrow view.  You do realize that its not "cold, damp and miserable outside" everywhere in the world.  Just because it may be that way where you live, doesn't mean its that way for everyone.   If you didn't know, its now summer in the southern hemisphere.  Australia, New Zealand, all of South America, etc... its all summer right now, not winter.   And while you may not like to go outside right now, lots of people do enjoy winter.  For one, in many area's its hunting season, so a lot of people are outside.  <br />
<br />
But the fact is, its the holiday season as well as end of the semester for anyone in college, that means projects and papers to finish up, finals to study for, moving back home for those that live in the dorms, etc.  Its also time for those of us that work to have crazy schedules trying to deal with the holiday season. Sure, WoW/EQ2 have played part in it, but they've also only been out for a month or so, no one has a clue how many will cancel their WOW/EQ2 account after the free month is up.<br />
<br />
You can say whatever you want to try rationalize your opinion, but I'll stick to the numbers that I've seen over the last 4 years in my guild:<br />
<br />
Raiding nights for the following months:<br />
<br />
Dec 2001: 18 (4 nights a week average)<br />
Jan 2002: 23 (5.2 nights a week average)<br />
<br />
Dec 2002: 16 (3.6 n/wk)<br />
Jan 2003: 23 (5.2 n/wk)<br />
<br />
Dec 2003: 19 (4.3 n/wk)<br />
Jan 2004: 29 (6.6 n/wk)<br />
<br />
As you can see, our turn out in Dec has always been poor such that we couldn't raid much, and every January we came back strong.   Finals, Holidays, work etc all caused it, and every year in January numbers picked right back up.</p>
	
	
	
