<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>weissblau</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Heyokah<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: May 2001<br />
	Location: Halas
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Even if a server merge is required, the population right now is not stable.  People are still leaving, and there's a good chance some folks who left will be back.  The time to do the merge is after the server population stabilizes, so you can tell whether to merge 2 servers into 1, or 3 into 1, or whatever.<br />
<br />
The only thing the current reduced population is hurting is high end raiders.  It's a boon for those people who don't raid high-end targets, don't have the uber gear, don't play six nights a week or eight hours at a time, etc. etc.  So the need to merge is hardly urgent.  Let the casual players have their fun for a while; if the high end folks have an enforced break, well, maybe they'll discover a whole world out there besides EQ.<br />
<br />
And, frankly, if enough of them get pissed off and leave EQ, maybe the tail will stop wagging the dog and they'll put some content in for the casual player.  I sure wouldn't miss the lvl 70 necro in a high-end raiding guild who intentionally trained me at tables in PoFire recently.</p>
	
	
	
