	<!-- message -->
	<p>I'd say two things:<br />
1) Server population has historically been low at this time of year. <br />
2) WoW is actually a very very viable alternative to EQ for people who were looking for another game to play.  I've started there and it's like the old days of EQ all over again.  The addiction, the sweaty palms in PvP action, the camaraderie with guildies.  I'm having more fun in that game than I've had in any game for years.  Meanwhile, I don't even think about activating my EQ account anymore.  That game still has the same problems that caused me to leave months ago.  That's just my own experience, but it may be an indicator that the server population may be permanently lower than before, even after the turn of the new year.</p>
	
	
	
