	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>While people may be playing other games at the moment, most probably still have their accounts on EQ1 still open, and consequently those servers are not going to be consolidated (their operation has been paid for, so to speak). I would think that any move to consolidate would be based on subscription base, not on active player base. In addition, there would likely be a delay between a fall off in subscriptions to server closings in order for the market to stabilize. You have to remember that Sony are in this to make money, so don't be surprised to see another expansion timed strategically to hit the shelves in the first quarter. I imagine that if they did that at that point, they could anticipate recapturing people disillusioned with WoW/EQ2 for whatever reason.</p>
	
	
	
