	<p>Now is the time to consolidate and it has little to do directly with eq2 and wow.  The low player count on most servers is a driver that leads people to quit playing on it's own.  The fact that it's harder to get groups, bazaar trading has dried up, guilds are struggling to assemble raid forces.....those are all frustrations that are forcing people out of EQ.  Many of those will now try one of the other games, not necessarily because they want to but because they are irritated with the low population that is left in EQ and are confident that SoE won't do anything until way later than it should.<br />
<br />
Consolidate.  Now.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
