	<!-- message -->
	<p>Honestly I believe that SOE considered that the mass exodus of players leaving to EQ2 and WoW.<br />
<br />
This is evident by the random rare uber items that drop off of trash as well as the elemental quality items dropping of of 1 groupable named NPC's in the new zones, not to mention the 1.5's that are for the most part attainable by a solid group of 24 or less in most cases.  They wanted to slightly level the playing field and allow 'uber guilds' access to more players by making it easier for newer players to become somewhat desireable, at least able to buff to 8k HP easily now.<br />
<br />
What I do believe is that EQ2 and WoW have struck a severe blow to the king of the MMPOLG's that may become fatal....  I hope not, but I fear that is the way of things to come.<br />
<br />
Give it time.  That is what I keep hearing.  Time is not a luxury of the dieing, and EQ may need more than time.<br />
<br />
That's my opinion.  Like it, love it or hate it....</p>
	
	
	
